  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (63c71b4 2022-09-12T00:05:14.033477Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nmake test match=test_optimism_relay\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nA nondescript crash occurs at this line: https://github.com/makerdao/dss-test/blob/637c1e0ac04d126690fbb81e17f9b402212254f9/src/tests/IntegrationTest.t.sol#L137\r\n\r\nThis test creates 2 network forks - one for mainnet and one for optimism. I set both the `OptimismDomain` and `MainnetDomain` to be persistent so they can be called from either fork.\r\n\r\nHigh level description of what's going on:\r\n\r\n1. It will deposit DAI through an existing bridge on mainnet, switch to optimism and relay the message.\r\n2. It will then withdraw the DAI back to mainnet.\r\n3. Queues up another message to do the same thing again.\r\n4. The second call to `optimism.relayL1ToL2()` fails. When inspecting it appears that switching back to the Optimism fork followed by any call to `vm` will cause the crash. I'm able to call into `vm` just fine in the test contract. It's only when I call into it from the `OptimismDomain` contract it crashes.",
